## 3. Ink Terminal Capabilities

### 3.1 Full-Screen Terminal Apps (Alternate Screen Buffer)

#### Native Ink Behavior
- Ink **does NOT natively support** fullscreen mode
- By default, Ink renders inline in the terminal (scrolls with history)
- Terminals cannot re-render text taller than window height

#### Solution: fullscreen-ink Package
```bash
npm install fullscreen-ink
# or
bun add fullscreen-ink
```

**Features:**
- Switches to alternate screen buffer on start
- Restores previous terminal content on exit
- Similar to vim/less behavior
- Uses escape sequences: `\e[?1049h` (enable) and `\e[?1049l` (disable)

**Usage Pattern:**
```typescript
import { render } from 'fullscreen-ink';

render(<App />);
// Automatically manages alternate screen buffer
```

### 3.2 Keyboard Input (Raw Mode & Key Events)

#### useInput Hook
Primary method for handling keyboard input:

```typescript
import { useInput } from 'ink';

function Component() {
  useInput((input, key) => {
    // input: raw character (e.g., 'a', 'b')
    // key: structured object with key info

    if (key.leftArrow) {
      // Handle left arrow
    }
    if (key.rightArrow) {
      // Handle right arrow
    }
    if (key.upArrow) {
      // Handle up arrow
    }
    if (key.downArrow) {
      // Handle down arrow
    }
    if (key.return) {
      // Handle Enter
    }
    if (key.escape) {
      // Handle Escape
    }
    if (key.ctrl && input === 'c') {
      // Handle Ctrl+C
    }
    if (key.shift && key.tab) {
      // Handle Shift+Tab (Ink 3+ improvement)
    }
    if (key.meta) {
      // Handle Meta/Command key
    }
  }, { isActive: true }); // isActive controls if hook captures input
}
```

#### Key Object Properties
```typescript
interface Key {
  upArrow: boolean;
  downArrow: boolean;
  leftArrow: boolean;
  rightArrow: boolean;
  return: boolean;
  escape: boolean;
  ctrl: boolean;
  shift: boolean;
  meta: boolean;
  tab: boolean;
  backspace: boolean;
  delete: boolean;
  pageDown: boolean;
  pageUp: boolean;
  // + kitty keyboard protocol support (Ink 6+):
  super: boolean;
  hyper: boolean;
  capsLock: boolean;
  numLock: boolean;
  eventType: 'press' | 'repeat' | 'release';
}
```

#### Raw Mode Details
- Ink automatically enables **raw mode** when needed
- Raw mode sends each keypress immediately (no buffering)
- Reference counting ensures raw mode stays enabled while any component needs it
- Handles ANSI escape sequence parsing automatically

#### Multiple useInput Hooks
- Use `isActive` option to control which hook receives input
- Prevents duplicate handling when multiple hooks exist
- Useful for modal dialogs, focus management

